article.headline: Northwestern St. 89, Texas State 71
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. (AP) -- Clifton Lee scored 16 points and Northwestern State defeated Texas State 89-71 to give coach Mike McConathy his 100th win with the Demons. Kerwin Forges added 12 points and Luke Rogers and Jermaine Wallaced had 10 apiece. The Demons (13-6, 6-1 Southland) were up 42-28 at the half and got 45 points off the bench. Northwestern also scored 28 points off Texas State turnovers. Charles Dotson led Texas State (2-15, 0-6) with a double-double of 24 points and 11 rebounds. Dotson was 11-of-18 from the field and made 2-of-4 free throws. Trevor Cook added 11 points for the Bobcats and Brandon Bush had 10.
